<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Seclinks</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-1q8mTJOASx8j1Au+a5WDVnPi2lkFfwwEAa8hDDdjZlpLegxhjVME1fgjWPGmkzs7" crossorigin="anonymous">
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>
<body>

  <section id="header">
    <nav id="app-nav" class="navbar navbar-default">
      <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class=navbar-header">
          <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">
              SecLinks
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
          <div class="header-text">
            <h1>Anonymous, temporary urls in seconds</h1>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="app-container" class="col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
          <%= yield %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="description">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What is seclinks?</h2> 
      <p>Seclinks makes it easy for anyone to create shortened URLs that delete themselves after a certain number of click-throughs or a certain amount of time. Expired links are removed from our database and resolve to a placeholder page on this site.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="highlights">
    <div class="container">
      <h3>How it works:</h3>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
          <h3>Create</h3>
          <p>Create a new link by specifying the URL you want to direct to and it's expiration. Expiration can be a time, a number of click-throughs, or both.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
          <h3>Share</h3>
          <p>Share your Seclink the way you would any other. The only difference is you control how long the link is good for.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
          <h3>Develop</h3>
          <p>Use our API to integrage Seclinks into your own projects or to create links without using the website.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</body>
</html>
